(81, 2, '2013-04-05 05:42:42', '2013-04-05 05:42:42', 'Growing Innovative Solar Energy Company seeks premium sales people for superior solutions, excellent income opportunities.', 'Inside Sales Consultant', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'inside-sales-consultant-2', '', '', '2013-04-05 07:02:10', '2013-04-05 07:02:10', '', 0, 'http://jobboard.1stsocial.com.au/?post_type=jobs&#038;p=81', 0, 'jobs', '', 0),
(82, 2, '2013-04-05 05:46:18', '2013-04-05 05:46:18', 'Growing Innovative Solar Energy Company seeks premium sales people for superior solutions, excellent income opportunities.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Melbourne Based - Service National Market</li>\r\n	<li>OTE $125k ++</li>\r\n	<li>Exceptional Product Quality</li>\r\n	<li>The Opportunity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWith the solar market in a state of flux due to seasonality and variable state based incentives, this company is uniquely positioned for national leverage and flexibility. They are currently You can shift your sales focus market to market across Australia as conditions change to protect your income and manage their growth.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Company</strong>\r\n\r\nThis company has quickly established itself as a major player with offices in most major centres in Australia as well as overseas partners. They are currently seeking a number of sales consultants to add to their growing team who can quickly service their growing base of qualified leads. They only sell the highest quality products, supported by 10-15 year warranties with competitiveness protected by unique buying arrangements.Training is intensive, differentiation is clear.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Accountabilities</strong>\r\n\r\nAs a Sales Consultant your responsibilities will include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Servicing a high volume of inbound leads</li>\r\n	<li>Explaining the benefits of featured products over competitive offers</li>\r\n	<li>Explaining the benefits of various government rebate schemes</li>\r\n	<li>Securing orders, deposits and handing over contract details to installers</li>\r\n	<li>The Successful Consultant</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWith several years of experience in the business to consumer solar market, you will have a track record of successful conversions. In fact, you will be successful enough to know that you just need to do your job to earn well into six figures. You will know the market, the technology and you will understand how government rebates drive demand. Ideally you will have experienced working in multiple state markets and be accustomed to some of the state by state variability in approaches. As most customers are in higher income brackets, you will be comfortable dealing with sophisticated and well informed buyers and will be nimble enough to adjust your approach in response to marketing campaigns and tactical competitive responses. If you see yourself as a leading Sales Consultant in solar, this is an opportunity to join a business with the best products, great prices and the rewards to support their market ambitions.\r\n\r\nPlease click on the ‘Apply Now’ button to submit your confidential application or telephone Andrew Thoseby on (03) 8617 8120 for further information. See ‘Job Search'' on www.facebook.com/1stexecutive where you can apply or register your details.', 'Inside Sales Consultant', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'inside-sales-consultant', '', '', '2013-04-09 00:16:31', '2013-04-09 00:16:31', '', 0, 'http://jobboard.1stsocial.com.au/?post_type=jobs&#038;p=82', 0, 'jobs', '', 0),
(84, 2, '2013-04-05 06:06:44', '2013-04-05 06:06:44', 'Project Engineer - 2 years experience ideally in waste water treatment process, needed for leader in design &amp; delivery of waste water solutions.\n<ul>\n	<li>Circa $70K plus super</li>\n	<li>Market Leader - water industry</li>\n	<li>Brisbane Office or work from home</li>\n</ul>\nOur client is a market leader in the manufacture of commercial scale water treatment and wastewater recycling systems. With activity in Australia and growth in overseas markets, they are entering a strong growth phase and are looking for the skills and aptitude of an experienced Project Engineer who enjoys the full circle process.\n\nYou will have 2+ years professional engineering design experience coupled with a degree in Mechanical Engineering. Your past experience may include exposure to the design of wastewater plants including process, hydraulic and mechanical/electrical components. An understanding of technical aspects of wastewater treatment in a variety of decentralized wastewater treatment technologies and water treatment technologies would be advantageous along with your ability to develop functional specifications for water and wastewater treatment systems. Your love of new technology will keep you interested in assessing new treatment technologies/processes and assisting in applying them to practical ecologically sustainable designs.\n\nReporting to the General Manager and working closely with a senior Engineer and small team of key staff, your main responsibilities will be Support to the team of onsite Treatment plant operators, trend analysis, identification of improved design/process and delivery of changes to standard product delivery whilst liaising with the client and coordinating all relevant subcontractors.\n\nYou will also conduct ongoing research and product/system development to meet evolving market opportunities and demands as well as continuous improvement focus across your areas of responsibility.\n\nYou will have excellent time management skills and the self discipline to ensure that you can manage the coordination of several projects concurrently. Attention to detail, initiative and accountability are all a must along with the flexibility to travel to remote sites\nIf you are looking for a role where you can make a difference, in a company that ismaking a difference - this is your next long term challenge.\n\nPlease click on the ‘Apply Now’ button below to submit your confidential application or telephone Suzanne Whitmarsh on (03) 8617 8110 for further information. Please see ‘Job Search'' on www.facebook.com/1stexecutive where you can apply and also register your details.', 'Project Engineer - Water', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'project-engineer-water-2', '', '', '2013-04-05 07:02:10', '2013-04-05 07:02:10', '', 0, 'http://jobboard.1stsocial.com.au/?post_type=jobs&#038;p=84', 0, 'jobs', '', 0),
