(86, 1, '2013-04-09 00:15:14', '2013-04-09 00:15:14', 'Project Engineer - 2 years experience ideally in waste water treatment process, needed for leader in design &amp; delivery of waste water solutions.\n<ul>\n	<li>Circa $70K plus super</li>\n	<li>Market Leader - water industry</li>\n	<li>Brisbane Office or work from home</li>\n</ul>\nOur client is a market leader in the manufacture of commercial scale water treatment and wastewater recycling systems. With activity in Australia and growth in overseas markets, they are entering a strong growth phase and are looking for the skills and aptitude of an experienced Project Engineer who enjoys the full circle process.\n\nYou will have 2+ years professional engineering design experience coupled with a degree in Mechanical Engineering. Your past experience may include exposure to the design of wastewater plants including process, hydraulic and mechanical/electrical components. An understanding of technical aspects of wastewater treatment in a variety of decentralized wastewater treatment technologies and water treatment technologies would be advantageous along with your ability to develop functional specifications for water and wastewater treatment systems. Your love of new technology will keep you interested in assessing new treatment technologies/processes and assisting in applying them to practical ecologically sustainable designs.\n\nReporting to the General Manager and working closely with a senior Engineer and small team of key staff, your main responsibilities will be Support to the team of onsite Treatment plant operators, trend analysis, identification of improved design/process and delivery of changes to standard product delivery whilst liaising with the client and coordinating all relevant subcontractors.\n\nYou will also conduct ongoing research and product/system development to meet evolving market opportunities and demands as well as continuous improvement focus across your areas of responsibility.\n\nYou will have excellent time management skills and the self discipline to ensure that you can manage the coordination of several projects concurrently. Attention to detail, initiative and accountability are all a must along with the flexibility to travel to remote sites\nIf you are looking for a role where you can make a difference, in a company that ismaking a difference - this is your next long term challenge.\n\nPlease click on the ‘Apply Now’ button below to submit your confidential application or telephone Suzanne Whitmarsh on (03) 8617 8110 for further information. Please see ‘Job Search'' on www.facebook.com/1stexecutive where you can apply and also register your details.', 'Project Engineer - Water', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '85-autosave', '', '', '2013-04-09 00:15:14', '2013-04-09 00:15:14', '', 85, 'http://jobboard.1stsocial.com.au/2013/04/05/85-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(92, 2, '2013-04-05 11:02:36', '2013-04-05 11:02:36', 'With our expanding water operations, we are looking for a Waste Water/Water Treatment Plant Operator to support the existing team in the operation of plants in Western Australia’s Pilbara Region and Central Queensland’s Bowen Basin on a FIFO basis.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>FIFO - need close access to a capital city airport</li>\r\n	<li>Two weeks on and two weeks off</li>\r\n	<li>Circa $80K plus super package</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong> The Opportunity</strong>\r\n\r\nReporting directly to the Mechanical Works Manager, you will be responsible for assisting in the routine operation and maintenance and minor works associated with packaged water and wastewater treatment plants which provide drinking water and handling domestic wastewater for mining and construction camps.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Company</strong>\r\n\r\nOur client is a market leader in the design and delivery of infrastructure solutions including water/wastewater, asset maintenance services and quarry products.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Accountabilities</strong>\r\n\r\nAs a Waste Water/Water Plant Operator your responsibilities will include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On site daily observations, Trend analysis &amp; reports to the Engineer</li>\r\n	<li>Reactive onsite maintenance as required</li>\r\n	<li>Preventative maintenance through the Work Order system</li>\r\n	<li>Client liaison</li>\r\n	<li>Operational handover to and from operators</li>\r\n	<li>Action Technical change requests</li>\r\n	<li>Contribute to Continuous improvement</li>\r\n	<li>Minor works and project construction and management of subcontractors</li>\r\n	<li>The Ideal Candidate</li>\r\n	<li>To be eligible you will have:</li>\r\n	<li>A Certificate III in Water/Wastewater Operations</li>\r\n	<li>A minimum of three years relevant industry experience</li>\r\n	<li>A Fitter or Plumber trade background</li>\r\n	<li>A demonstrated ability to work autonomously on remote sites</li>\r\n	<li>A demonstrated commitment to meet operational service and WH&amp;S standards</li>\r\n	<li>A current drivers licence and clear Police Record</li>\r\n	<li>The ability to interpret P&amp;IDS &amp; construction drawings</li>\r\n	<li>Strong problem solving ability under pressure</li>\r\n	<li>Be computer literate - Microsoft suite (Excel/Word/Project)</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent communication skills verbal &amp; written</li>\r\n	<li>The ability to write timely, relevant and accurate reports</li>\r\n	<li>The ability to deal with issues/actions promptly and to communicate effectively</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent time management skills</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease note: there will be a requirement to travel and work outside normal working hours. Roster is 2 weeks on and 2 weeks off with four weeks Annual Leave.\r\nPlease click on the ‘Apply Now’ button below to submit your confidential application or telephone Suzanne Whitmarsh on (03) 8617 8110 for further information. Please see ‘Job Search'' on www.facebook.com/1stexecutive where you can apply and also register your details.', 'Waste Water Treatment Plant Operator', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'waste-water-treatment-plant-operator', '', '', '2013-04-09 00:19:13', '2013-04-09 00:19:13', '', 0, 'http://jobboard.1stsocial.com.au/?post_type=jobs&#038;p=92', 0, 'jobs', '', 0),
(93, 1, '2013-04-09 00:20:17', '2013-04-09 00:20:17', 'With our expanding water operations, we are looking for a Waste Water/Water Treatment Plant Operator to support the existing team in the operation of plants in Western Australia’s Pilbara Region and Central Queensland’s Bowen Basin on a FIFO basis.\n<ul>\n	<li>FIFO - need close access to a capital city airport</li>\n	<li>Two weeks on and two weeks off</li>\n	<li>Circa $80K plus super package</li>\n</ul>\n<strong> The Opportunity</strong>\n\nReporting directly to the Mechanical Works Manager, you will be responsible for assisting in the routine operation and maintenance and minor works associated with packaged water and wastewater treatment plants which provide drinking water and handling domestic wastewater for mining and construction camps.\n\n<strong>The Company</strong>\n\nOur client is a market leader in the design and delivery of infrastructure solutions including water/wastewater, asset maintenance services and quarry products.\n\n<strong>The Accountabilities</strong>\n\nAs a Waste Water/Water Plant Operator your responsibilities will include:\n<ul>\n	<li>On site daily observations, Trend analysis &amp; reports to the Engineer</li>\n	<li>Reactive onsite maintenance as required</li>\n	<li>Preventative maintenance through the Work Order system</li>\n	<li>Client liaison</li>\n	<li>Operational handover to and from operators</li>\n	<li>Action Technical change requests</li>\n	<li>Contribute to Continuous improvement</li>\n	<li>Minor works and project construction and management of subcontractors</li>\n	<li>The Ideal Candidate</li>\n	<li>To be eligible you will have:</li>\n	<li>A Certificate III in Water/Wastewater Operations</li>\n	<li>A minimum of three years relevant industry experience</li>\n	<li>A Fitter or Plumber trade background</li>\n	<li>A demonstrated ability to work autonomously on remote sites</li>\n	<li>A demonstrated commitment to meet operational service and WH&amp;S standards</li>\n	<li>A current drivers licence and clear Police Record</li>\n	<li>The ability to interpret P&amp;IDS &amp; construction drawings</li>\n	<li>Strong problem solving ability under pressure</li>\n	<li>Be computer literate - Microsoft suite (Excel/Word/Project)</li>\n	<li>Excellent communication skills verbal &amp; written</li>\n	<li>The ability to write timely, relevant and accurate reports</li>\n	<li>The ability to deal with issues/actions promptly and to communicate effectively</li>\n	<li>Excellent time management skills</li>\n</ul>\nPlease note: there will be a requirement to travel and work outside normal working hours. Roster is 2 weeks on and 2 weeks off with four weeks Annual Leave.\nPlease click on the ‘Apply Now’ button below to submit your confidential application or telephone Suzanne Whitmarsh on (03) 8617 8110 for further information. Please see ‘Job Search'' on www.facebook.com/1stexecutive where you can apply and also register your details.', 'Waste Water Treatment Plant Operator', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '92-autosave', '', '', '2013-04-09 00:20:17', '2013-04-09 00:20:17', '', 92, 'http://jobboard.1stsocial.com.au/2013/04/05/92-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
